Students must choose their specialization (Pointe or Dance & Physicality) during their first semester and cannot switch between specializations in future semesters.

Applicants need an Ontario Secondary School Diploma or equivalent, with a grade 12 English (C or U). For dance program applicants, they must have a minimum of intermediate level training in classical ballet for 5-7 years and pointe work experience. Mature students (19 years old or above without an OSSD) may take the Admissions Assessment for English or consider upgrading to achieve required English credits. Course exemptions are possible with college or university credits. International students should apply through the George Brown College Online Application System and visit the International Admissions page for country-specific requirements. Domestic students should apply through Ontario Colleges. For dance program inquiries, contact Kia Kotsanis at dance@georgebrown.ca or education@balletjorgen.ca. Applicants can call the Contact Centre at 416-415-2000 (TTY 1-877-515-5559) or long distance 1-800-265-2002 for more information. International students may also contact recruitment representatives specialized by country of origin through a virtual meeting or inquiry.

The program is offered through George Brown College's School of Media and Performing Arts and runs in partnership with Ballet Jörgen. The classes take place at Casa Loma Campus, located at 160 Kendal Ave., Toronto, Ontario, Canada. Campus tours are offered regularly. Related programs include Commercial Dance (P106) and Dance Performance Preparation (P101). Students receive training in ballet, contemporary, jazz dance, vocals, acting, composition, and choreography daily. Prospective students can book campus tours or info sessions, sign up to receive tailored resources for application, and check out the virtual tour. Contact information is not provided in the text.
